            <div class="article_col-main article_col-main-left article_main">
              <div class="article-body" itemprop="articleBody">
                    <p> FLINT, Michigan — Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton called for &quot;action now&quot; to combat the toxic water crisis here Sunday in a speech to a packed congregation. </p>
                
              
              
              
                    <p> &quot;This has to be a national priority,&quot; Clinton said at the House of Prayer Missionary Baptist Church. &quot;What happened in Flint is immoral. The children of Flint are just as precious as the children of any part of America.&quot; </p>
                
              
              
              
                
              
              
              
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
